My brother was killed because of your amiitum. The silver that he took away in the name of La-qepum - surely he was killed for the silver for the iron that you gave to him. Go and sue for the blood-money for my brother.
The Colony passed a verdict that until they acquire the blood money for Salim-Assur's son, no one may go via Tawiniya, and no one, either among the great men or among the small men, may carry out his wishes.
