He packed the copper (to go) from Durhumit to Purushaddum, and he packed his own donkey to (go) as far as Wahsusana, and then I led them (the remaining donkeys) out with the help of the guard posts on the Ulama road and I returned.
Four shekels per (donkey) came on as fees until Ulama. I paid 5 shekels of silver for the (cart) transport. I paid 10 shekels of silver to the Colony. The (expenses) for us until Ulama amounted to 1 shekel. The (expenses) for each of us from Durhumit amounted to one and half a shekel.
I and my brothers have met with him at least five times, in Purushaddum, in Ulama or in Wahsusana.
The sikkatum has withdrawn but the silver is delayed. If there is trade, write to me and I will make 5-6 minas of silver and send it to you[ <gap> ] settles down, and[ <gap> the price] of copper in Ulama is 17 shekels per mina, and in Salatuwar good copper is sold at a rate of 13 shekels per mina. If I am to pack 10 talents of copper to Salatuwar or Ulama, then send me some donkeys so that I will not have to buy donkeys. Let your message reach me with the first traveller and make donkeys travel here.
