Uṣur-ša-Ištar son of Ili-imitti
If losses occur in your land, you are to investigate them and recompense us
If there is bloodshed in your land, you are to extradite the murderers to us, so that we may slay them
The black dog lies in wait on the mound. It lingers for the lonely caravan. Its eyes peer around for a handsome youth
The cold has caught up with us, and the caravan has suffered hunger.
As to the fact that I wrote to you, saying: 'At the beginning of spring I shall write to you, so you can come here' – do not be angry with me! The cold has caught up with us <gap>
There is a lot of cold (snow), and it is not feasible for the donkey to walk.
Now the winter has caught up with you in Uršu. Since there is a lot of snow
I want to enter Purušhaddum before the cold sets in. The winter must not catch up with me.
Do not be angry. Alas, fear is placed in the heart of the land, and for that reason I have been held back for a couple of months. As soon as the land settles down, I will send the rest of your money with the first travellers (leaving).
the country is in turmoil
the word of the land to its place may return
the country is in turmoil, and I haven't brought you the tin you gave me for (buying) the lulum-metal
