Seal the [object], give it to Eniš-tarim and send him with the bātiqum that will come ahead of the caravan
Take a mina or so of tiri-silver out of our father's funds and send them here with a bātiqum or with my servants
Pay attention to the missives from the City that Ennanum brought to you, and give it to the very first express transport so they may bring it. He should leave with the first travellers to depart
Send me a report concerning all my instructions with a bātiqum to inform me
If indeed that opportunity was open for me and I would indeed be free to go there, would then until this day, when Aluwa came, at least 10 minas of silver not have come to you quickly with a bātiqum?
and send Aluwa with a bātiqum
Take care to send me the silver in your possession as well as what you may ask for from brother and friend with an express transport
to my first servant
healthy donkey
