In accordance with your message (about the) 10 talents (300 kg) of copper, we hired some Kanešites and they will bring it to you in a wagon <gap> pay in all 21 shekels of silver to the Kanešite transporters. Three bags of copper are under your seal – in all a wagon(load) <gap> Here, he remunerated Puzur-Aššur 5 minas of copper for their fodder. We paid 5 2/3 minas of copper for the wagon
The colony has detained Šarrrum-Su'en for a single day. His wagons have left ten days ahead of him
One nāru, 2 pots of kiššanu-seed and 3 wagonloads of straw are with the [<gap>]kaššiya priest, our guest
Have the copper transported to Šalatuwar and send me the silver, the proceeds of the copper. [x+]4 1/2 talents of šikku-copper is owed by Puzur-Su'en, the Hahhe'an. Leave behind that copper, make him pay, and buy it in a wagon so that he can send it to Purušhaddum
