You have borrowed half a mina and 6 shekels of silver from the (year of) the eponym Dadiya son of Šu-Ilabrat. I seized you in Amkuwa, where you said: 'Go up to Hattuš and produce a (debt) note with your witness for me'. So I went up to Hattuš, but your representatives did not give me their word. Tell my representatives: 'If he refuses to pay the money there, it will make me angry'. Let your message reach me in Hanaknak.
