Out of the 20 talents and 15 minas of coppers that they will pay in Wahšušana on my behalf, I handed over 10 talents and 55 minas of good copper to Aššur-malik in accordance with your message. 10 minas I sealed with my seal today, and I am bringing it to you. (As for) the remainder of your copper – 9 talents and 20 minas – return your servant so that he may bring it to you <gap>
1 1/2 minas of good copper for Ali-ahum. 1 mina of good copper at his disposal. 2/3 minas of šikkum-copper for the attorney. 6 shekels of good copper for his mūṣium in Aliašša. I personally balanced 4 shekels (for) his lodgings in Daša. 40 shekels of copper for transporting. 1/4 shekel (of silver) for the guards and the bridge.
I paid 1/2 minas of good copper for lodgings. I hired a servant and I gave him 1 mina of good copper until the bridge. The man was booked for 2 1/2 shekels of tin in Diša
