To the envoys of the City and the Kaneš Colony from the Wahšušana Colony. The king of Wašhaniya has written to us, saying: 'I have seized the throne of my father. Let me swear an oath'. We answered: 'The Kaneš Colony is our [lord]. We shall write so that they may write either to you (directly) or to us. Two men from the Land will come to you and then they can make you swear the oath'. It is up to you now. Let your orders come here.
refined silver
