Since there is no king in Ulama, there is turmoil and there is no traffic. I will check things in Wahšušana. I will act according to your instructions. Also, I held back the donkeys. In ten days I will say: 'When will the road will open?' (and) if they have not taken away the donkeys, then I will return them to you
