From Wahšušana to Šalatuwar 1 5/6 minas 5 shekels came on as our fees, donkey fodder and lodgings. In addition, they deducted 1/3 mina for each donkey at the bridge. 2 minas of copper for donkey fodder in Šalatuwar.
Regarding the fact that they have not sent any money until this day – the palace in Tuhapiya held me back and had me delayed for ten days. I came into Wahšušana, but the palace brought about trick, and they returned my goods from the caravan and so I turned toward Šalatuwar. I sent off Su'en-pilah for the day they will leave for Purušhaddum.
I have completed 3000 talents of copper for the ruler of Wahšušana
