To Assur-emuqi from Ma~i-ili. I am carrying 4 talents of tin and extras sealed in the City. 250 textiles- thereof 20 textiles of good quality, and 17 textiles of good quality belonging to your ikribum- as well as 13 black donkeys, all of this I am bringing to you. Your goods are well. Your donkeys are well. Do not worry about a thing. Take care and send I mina of silver in advance of me to Hahhum. If you are my father, buy 5 shekels of silver worth of small goods, seal it with your seal, and send it to me. We have just left Eluhhut.
