Speak to Adad-sulùli, thus (says) Sú-Bèlim: your copper has been sold at a rate of 72 1/2 shekels of copper per shekel of silver, the donkeys (sold) for 62 minas of copper. In accordance with your instructions I took my (share of the) copper. I paid 2 minas of excellent copper for barley and straw as long as (the donkeys) were standing.
The plenary session of the kàrum of WahsuAana passed this verdict: date: month 10, year-eponym Sú-Suen son of Babulum; if Baltua has taken copper beloaging to Adad-sulitli in Salatuar (Adad-sulúli will present his terms and they will produce their witnesses).
In mutual agreement Adad-sulúlf and Baltua seized us, and Adad-sulúli said to Baltua: "You withheld in Salatuar 5 1/2 talents of refined copper from my transporter Samas-ennam. If it is proved that this copper is mine, you will pay me (silver for my copper) at a rate of 30 shekels of copper per shekel of silver, in accordance with the kârum verdict."
Adad-sulúli will give 10 talents of refined copper to Iddi(n)-Suen in Purughattum, and at the very moment (he accepts) his copper, Iddi(n)-Suen will pay Adad-sulúli 12 minas of refined silver.
Speak to Iddi(n)-Assur, thus Puzur-Istar: I acted as your representative and collected the 4 talents of poor copper that Adad-sulúli owed you; the copper has been paid for various expenses of yours.
When Assur-tab turns up from a trip to the City, Adad-sulúli will put before him 1 talent of tin, still bearing the City's seals, and they will divide it into three parts and Assur-tab will take 20 minas of tin; after 2 months from the day when he received the tin, he will pay to Adad-sulúli in Turhumit 3 talents 20 minas of broken fine copper.
Adad-sulúli has 53 minas of copper from Ninasa as a claim on Imlikaya, Gaza, and Nuhsatum. (Gaza) will pay within one year from month 5, year eponym Assur-imitti. The obligation to pay back the copper is upon whoever among them is solvent. If he does not pay, he will add interest according to the rate decreed by the karum. This copper is (the amount) after 30 minas had been paid; on behalf of Gaza; and the 53 minas of copper are also on behalf of Gaza; Imlikâya is guarantor.
