I have written to you many times, saying: 'The palace is cheating the colony – inform the colony!' You have informed the colony. (But) your report has not returned to me. Send it here! (The palace) seized the caravan and the ašium, and so they not willing to release us. You favored the colony immediately and made me stay (here) till this very day
They seized us in the palace in your (pl.) presence. Talia said: "Aššur-imittī and Šu-Ištar cheated me in a lowly way and did not want to give me my textiles". Although they did not arrest me with contraband, and I did not buy things that are not approved by the gods of Kaneš, the colony is saying: "we will not support him in his guilt and his evilness". Today, kārum is always compelling me to give offerings instead of inform us. (Moreover) our friends (also) do not inform us. My dear father and lord, I am not scared to stay (here). Under no circumstances should the damned palace write here without your knowledge and shall not kill us. If the colony does not take care of us, spend about 10 minas of my silver, (and) pull me through (this) hard predicament for your reputation
from the hamuštum-week of Šu-Ištar son of Aššur-bāni
