To the Kanesh colony from the Tamnija colony: Envoys from the Durhumit colony brought the king of Tamnija a present for (the ceremony of) swearing the oath, but he said to the envoys: 'Where are the envoys of my fathers, of the Kanesh colony? They should come here and then I shall take the oath from them!' He treats us with contempt and says: 'I shall build a city!' <gap> We brought him a present. We have informed you. They should not treat a traveller with contempt.
To the king of Sirmija: Thus says the Kanesh colony: one mina of refined silver and three shekels of gold. Abiaa and Agua are our envoys.
