Šumi-abiya owes Elamma 1⁄2 mina refined silver. He will add as interest 1 shekel per mina per month from the week of Ili-nāda.
Aššur-taklāku and Amur-ilī owe Aššur-taklāku 1 mina 5 shekels refined silver. They (lit. he) will add as interest 2 shekels per mina per month from the week of Ennam-Aššur.
Puzur-Anna owes Šū-Bēlum 25⁄6 minas refined silver. He will add 11⁄2 shekels as interest per month per mina from the week of Aššur-mālik and Innaya.
Waldi-lum s. Šū-Bēlum must not return to Enna-Suen s. Aššur-nīšu or his children for anything.
Hazubala owes Šū-Bēlum 1 mina silver. From the week of Pūšu-kēn and Zupa (in) Month II, he will pay 15 shekels silver at harvest. He will pay back 15 shekels at the festival of Anna. He will pay (the remaining) 1⁄2 mina back in the spring. If he does not pay (by then), he will add 3 shekels per mina per month.
